🟢 Language ➡ Java
🟢 Topic ➡ Control Statement   


🧭 Control Statements in C
Control statements change the flow of execution in a program.

✅ 1. Decision Control Statements
Used to make decisions based on conditions.

🔹 if Statement
Executes code only if the condition is true.
if (condition) {
    // true block
}


🔹 if...else
Choose between two blocks based on condition.
if (condition) {
    // true block
} else {
    // false block
}



🔹 else if Ladder
Checks multiple conditions in sequence.
if (cond1) {
    // block 1
} else if (cond2) {
    // block 2
} else {
    // default block
}


🔹 Ternary Operator ? :
Shorthand for if...else.
(condition) ? value_if_true : value_if_false;




🔹 switch-case
Used when multiple conditions depend on a single expression.

switch(expression) {
    case constant1:
        // code
        break;
    case constant2:
        // code
        break;
    default:
        // default code
}



🔁 2. Iterative (Looping) Statements
Used to execute a block of code repeatedly.

🔹 for loop
for(initialization; condition; increment) {
    // loop body
}



🔹 while loop
while(condition) {
    // loop body
}



🔹 do-while loop
do {
    // loop body
} while(condition);



🚀 3. Jumping Statements
Used to jump from one part of the code to another.

🔹 break
Exits the loop or switch immediately.

🔹 continue
Skips the current iteration and moves to the next.


